lenders.loan_because:
Why do I need to diversify the services in the shop of my family .. Helping to grow the number of customers and therefore also the budget of the video store and get out of this difficult situation we find ourselves in today.

 Unfair competition from piracy has put us in the present situation due to the fact that we have resolved to stick to the original tapes and DVDs.

 We were the first home video store in our neighborhood, since we are the largest and currently the last remaining segment of this in our neighborhood.
lenders.occupational_info:
I'm 42 years old. We create our video rental store in 1991. When we were the first store in our neighborhood to work with rental VHS tapes .. Unfortunately with unfair competition from DVD piracy, today we are in a financial position not very good. And we're hard to keep our trade. So we try to diversify trade, putting other services available to our customers. We now offer computer maintenance and internet access for residents of the neighborhood through some computers we have in our store. We also created a micro office, where we do services for people who have no computer knowledge. So we have a exencial service to the people who live in the neighborhood and do not like to leave them without this kind of service with a possible closure of our shop VOYAGER VIDEO. 

Our location is in the Centenário  neighborhood in the city of Duque de Caxias, State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. 

Rua Joaquim Nabuco, 113, c store, CEP: 25030-130

I was accepted for the UNESCO 7th international Human rights leadership youth forum which will be in August 4-14,2011; in the university of Connecticut.
the travel and visa costs are on participants; they cost about 4000$ 
I'm from Lebanon, my parents are divorced, i live with my young sister with my mom , we don't know anything about our dad since 2009; i study nutrition and dietetics, and I work as student work in the university to pay my tuition .
i contacted all NGOs and the US embassy, and the UNESCO and all of them replied that they don't have funds

 I am the only one chosen from Lebanon , from a pool of 800 applicants all around the world !!

Hope to get a help from you to be part of this amazing event :)
lenders.occupational_info:
University of Connecticut
UNESCO Chair & Institute of Comparative Human Rights
Amii Omara-Otunnu,
D. Phil. (Oxon)
UNESCO Chair-holder
& Executive Director
An Equal Opportunity Employer
233 Glenbrook Road Unit 4124
Storrs, Connecticut 06269-4124
Telephone: (860)486-0647
Fascimile: (860)486-2545
e-mail: unescochair@uconn.edu
web: ww.unescochair.uconn.edu
May 31, 2011
Re: Sponsorship of Human Rights Leader – Farah Abou El Sel
Warm Greetings,
I write to inform you that a young human rights leader from Lebanon has been selected and has
fulfilled all registration requirements to participate in the 2011 International Leadership
Programme: A Global Intergenerational Training Forum, sponsored by the UNESCO Chair &
Institute of Comparative Human Rights. Farah Abou El Sel from Lebanon has been selected
from a pool of over 700 applicants from more than 85 nations and representing all 6 continents,
to participate in the Forum from August 5 - August 14, 2011 on the University of Connecticut
campus in Storrs, Connecticut, USA.
The Forum, apart from providing young leaders with skills and tools to be effective in their
various areas of advocacy and promotion of human rights, aims to present the participants with a
human face of the United States and to foster understanding between the people of this country
and other regions of the world.
The UNESCO Chair & Institute of Comparative Human Rights will provide all Forum
participants with housing, meals, ground transportation in Connecticut during the Forum, as well
as resource materials and a certificate of participation. As you are aware, air travel from most
countries to the United States is quite costly. As such, most of the participants especially those
traveling from developing nations will find it extremely impossible to bear the costs of air travel.
Thus I would like to appeal to you to consider assisting partially, or sponsoring in whole the air
travel for this outstanding young human rights leader from Lebanon. I hope you share the view
that human rights is a means of cultivating cooperation between the US and other parts of the
world and will consider assisting and facilitating this participant in attending the Forum.
Please feel free to contact me with any questions you might have about the Forum, or anything
else regarding this matter.
Thank you for your consideration,
Amii Omara-Otunnu, D. Phil. (Oxon.),
UNESCO Chair-holder & Executive Director,
Executive Director, UConn-ANC Partnership,
Professor of History
